        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Channeling skill determins if a spell is interrupted or not. Another factor seems to be your level vs the level of the spell you are casting. The greater the number, the less chance it will be interrupted. </P><P>     May also want to try backing up in a corner or at least onto a wall so as to negate knock backs. EQ will calculate the position you were in when you begin to cast a spell and your position after it is cast. Again, the greater the number the less chance the spell has on going off.</P><P>     Not sure what your level is, but may want to try to buy or get some boots of concentration. They are 50 hp and 3% to channeling. Helps a bit. I have seen them drop on the 1st floor in Ssra.</P><P><BR>Veesh<BR>Warlock<BR>Shards of Avalon<BR>Xegony</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

