        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I've had similar problems - what is probably happening is that you are not completely stopped when you begin to cast your spell (especially while kiting druid-style) so that even though you think your stopped, you slide a tiny bit and get your spell interrupted, the higher you get, the less trouble you'll have with this as your higher skill will compensate for the sliding.</P><P><font size=1><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=54401" target="_blank">Azumaan</a></b><br>33 Erudite Necromancer<br>Silver Faith<br>Mithaniel Marr</font id=size1><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

