        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         When you stop running to start casting, count to 3, then cast. You don't have to count slowly, just say 1 2 3 in your head (or out loud if ya wanna make your housemates wonder) and then start the cast. I used to get interupted all the time on dial-up until I started doing this. It became such a habit that I still do it now on cable. But, I very very rarely get interuptions now, even when getting hit. My channeling is pretty high tho. In the lower levels I did alot of melee while casting specifically so my channeling would be high.<BR>Always wondered tho if the spell class made a difference. I can still get a tap off after being hit 4 times in a row, but root seems to only take one hit to get interrupted. Root casts faster than my current tap, so it doesn't seem to be the casting time. Just curious if anyone else has noticed anything similar.</P><P>To avoid critism<br><BR>say nothing<br><BR>do nothing<br><BR>be nothing.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
