         You can add one more verification to the "tap turn" method. I learned about this a couple of months ago and don't get interrupts 99% of the time now. </P><P>I'm not sure what the rationale behind being able to cast while turning but not while moving is (seems like movement is movement... why should I be able to cast any better when turning in place?) but I'm not going to argue with it! <img src=icon_smile_approve.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>Bene Moriore!<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

